1
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:41,200
(Touch Your Heart)

2
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:46,353
I'm more scared about seeing you
disappear from by my side,

3
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:49,786
rather than missing this opportunity
because of a scandal.

4
00:00:49,866 --> 00:00:51,000
So…

5
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,166
Let's start again.

6
00:01:00,666 --> 00:01:03,066
You're really going to
let me go like this?

7
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,533
Even if you might…

8
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:13,700
…never see me again?

9
00:01:36,466 --> 00:01:37,700
Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

10
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:48,666
I love you.

11
00:02:22,766 --> 00:02:24,666
(Episode 15)

12
00:02:28,066 --> 00:02:30,386
We're here already.

13
00:02:30,466 --> 00:02:32,200
Why does my place
have to be so near?

14
00:02:37,033 --> 00:02:40,720
I don't want to go home tonight.

15
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:45,720
I just want to stay with you.

16
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,833
To be honest with you... so do I.

17
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,600
Can I leave, after
watching you fall asleep?

18
00:03:09,533 --> 00:03:12,020
I don't fall asleep easily.

19
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:13,253
Then even better.

20
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:16,420
That way, I get to
see you much longer.

21
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:20,753
You know, I was never
bothered by my insomnia,

22
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:23,753
but after breaking up with you,

23
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:28,353
it was a bit hard for me.

24
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:30,753
Because all through those
sleepless nights,

25
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,933
I'd end up thinking about you.

26
00:03:37,066 --> 00:03:40,620
When was it the hardest for you?

27
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,120
Actually, forget I even asked.

28
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,600
You were probably fine,
because you were so busy.

29
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:46,953
Who says so,

30
00:03:47,033 --> 00:03:48,786
that I was perfectly fine?

31
00:03:48,866 --> 00:03:52,453
It was hard for me every night,
and every morning.

32
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:55,686
Even while at work,
or at the court…

33
00:03:55,766 --> 00:03:58,753
Every moment was hard for me.

34
00:03:58,833 --> 00:03:59,820
Really?

35
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:01,753
It really was hard for you?

36
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:05,586
What, is that something to be
so excited about?

37
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:06,953
Of course.

38
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,400
That just proves
how much you love me.

39
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:13,333
Somehow, that puts me at ease.

40
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:27,553
Let's never break up again.

41
00:04:27,633 --> 00:04:30,320
Promise me that

42
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,700
you won't ever let go of my hand.

43
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,186
Alright.

44
00:04:36,266 --> 00:04:37,633
I promise.

45
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:42,453
I will never let go of this hand.

46
00:04:42,533 --> 00:04:46,333
And I will protect you,
Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

47
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:53,620
The reason why
I left you was because

48
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:56,553
these are important times for you

49
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:59,220
and I didn't want to be
your burden.

50
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:01,686
And even now,
I don't want that at all.

51
00:05:01,766 --> 00:05:04,953
So in order to protect you,

52
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:08,520
I think we should be extra careful
about seeing each other.

53
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,720
Extra careful?

54
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:15,186
Yes. We can't risk another
picture of us like last time,

55
00:05:15,266 --> 00:05:17,853
so let's refrain from
meeting outside.

56
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:20,553
Let's either meet here
at your place, or mine.

57
00:05:20,633 --> 00:05:23,833
Or somewhere else that's enclosed.

58
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:31,453
Enclosed?

59
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:32,566
Yes.

60
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:38,133
Somewhere secretive and quiet,
with only the two of us.

61
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:49,766
May I stay for the night?

62
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,520
I won't ever cross this line.

63
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,953
I promised you, didn't I?

64
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:10,400
That I'll protect you.

65
00:06:11,366 --> 00:06:12,900
Well, uh…

66
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,466
Thank you so much for
protecting me.

67
00:07:11,566 --> 00:07:12,786
Good morning, Mr. Kwon.

68
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:14,466
Yes, good morning.

69
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:19,420
It must've been uncomfortable
sleeping like that.

70
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,020
It's fine.

71
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:22,486
What's your schedule like today?

72
00:07:22,566 --> 00:07:24,386
I'm quite free today.

73
00:07:24,466 --> 00:07:29,553
We start shooting at about 1,
so I should be done by 7.

74
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:32,420
Then we can have dinner together.

75
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,120
I'll call you as soon as I'm done.

76
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,200
Alright.

77
00:07:37,366 --> 00:07:38,633
Who is that
so early in the morning?

78
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:43,453
It's my manager!

79
00:07:43,533 --> 00:07:44,720
- What do we do?
- Yoon-seo!

80
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,800
He might get the wrong idea
when he sees you here!

81
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,986
Maybe we can pretend that

82
00:07:50,066 --> 00:07:51,620
- we're not here?
- Yoon-seo!

83
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:52,953
No.

84
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:53,953
He knows the passcode.

85
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:56,186
If I don't answer him,
he'll probably let himself in.

86
00:07:56,266 --> 00:07:58,186
- What do we do?
- Passcode? Why?

87
00:07:58,266 --> 00:07:59,220
Even if he is your manager,

88
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:01,000
- you have your privacy…
- I'm coming in!

89
00:08:08,266 --> 00:08:09,886
Hide in here, for the time being.

90
00:08:09,966 --> 00:08:11,533
But, uh… Ms. Oh Jin-sim!

91
00:08:16,266 --> 00:08:17,353
Oh what?

92
00:08:17,433 --> 00:08:18,953
So you were up already.

93
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:22,520
I thought you were still in bed.

94
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:26,753
Well, uh… I was using the blender,

95
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,500
and I guess
I didn't hear the bell.

96
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:33,453
So… Why are you here so early?

97
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:35,086
Don't I start at 1 o'clock?

98
00:08:35,166 --> 00:08:36,953
I got a call that
there's been some changes.

99
00:08:37,033 --> 00:08:38,453
You start at eleven now,

100
00:08:38,533 --> 00:08:39,853
so we need to get going now.

101
00:08:39,933 --> 00:08:41,953
Oh, I see. Sure.

102
00:08:42,033 --> 00:08:44,420
Then I'll get ready and
come right down.

103
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,953
You wait in the car.
I'll be right there.

104
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:48,833
- Sure, make it quick.
- Alright.

105
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,886
Oh, that's right.

106
00:08:53,966 --> 00:08:55,833
Can I use the bathroom?

107
00:08:58,033 --> 00:08:59,033
Hyuk-jun!

108
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:01,553
What is it?

109
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,220
I'm sorry,

110
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,820
but can you not use the bathroom?

111
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:06,620
- But why?
- Huh?

112
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,053
Well, uh… Just!

113
00:09:09,133 --> 00:09:10,653
Yoon-seo, I'm sorry,

114
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:13,320
but I'm about to burst.

115
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,320
So please excuse me.

116
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,353
- Hyuk-jun, but…
- Please.

117
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:18,300
- Hyuk-jun! Hyuk-jun!
- Please excuse me.

118
00:09:27,633 --> 00:09:28,653
Yoon-seo,

119
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:30,886
are you going to just stand there?

120
00:09:30,966 --> 00:09:33,020
Oh. Sorry, Hyuk-jun.

121
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,086
- Right?
- Yeah.

122
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:36,300
If you're so sorry to my bladder,
then off you go.

123
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:38,500
- Sure.
- Now!

124
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,700
Who's there?

125
00:10:20,566 --> 00:10:21,600
Mr. Kwon!

126
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:25,153
Ah, yes.

127
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:26,900
The Prosecution Service…?

128
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:33,833
Well, uh…

129
00:10:35,633 --> 00:10:36,800
Are you alright?

130
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:42,333
Uh… Mr. Kwon?

131
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:47,920
I'm alright. Uh…

132
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,133
I was going to
take a shower anyway.

133
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,466
(Shingil 3-dong
Morning Football Club)

134
00:10:52,466 --> 00:10:53,600
Oh no…

135
00:10:57,466 --> 00:11:01,333
At least Hyuk-jun had
a spare shirt in his car.

136
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,720
I'll wash this and
return it to you later.

137
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,920
So what's going on?

138
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,686
Why are you here, Mr. Kwon,
so early in the morning?

139
00:11:11,766 --> 00:11:13,400
Don't tell me…

140
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:16,620
You spent the night here?

141
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:17,620
- No!
- Yes.

142
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:18,686
No? Yes?

143
00:11:18,766 --> 00:11:19,853
No, yes?!

144
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:20,953
There's my answer there.

145
00:11:21,033 --> 00:11:21,953
But Mr. Kwon,

146
00:11:22,033 --> 00:11:24,753
while I did say I'll approve of
you two dating,

147
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,920
this is… This is just not right!

148
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,066
Hyuk-jun!

149
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:31,153
Mr. Kwon, you should get going.

150
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:33,420
You'll be tight for time since
you need to go home first.

151
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,800
So come on. Let's go.

152
00:11:36,566 --> 00:11:37,600
Then…

153
00:11:38,366 --> 00:11:39,753
Mr. Kwon?

154
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:41,200
I'm not done…

155
00:11:43,566 --> 00:11:45,833
What's she going to do?

156
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,400
Here.

157
00:11:56,066 --> 00:11:58,500
- Bye.
- I'm off, then.

158
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:16,120
Hyuk-jun, how could you be
so mean to him?

159
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,586
When he got all soaked,
because of you?

160
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:20,353
Yoon-seo,

161
00:12:20,433 --> 00:12:21,786
Mr. Kwon may have been
soaked because of me,

162
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:24,453
but for me,
this is a complete shock!

163
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:26,720
You haven't even dated him for
long enough,

164
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:29,253
and you call him here?

165
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,720
Then what?

166
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:31,820
Should we just see each other
on the streets?

167
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:32,920
You want people to
snap photos of us?

168
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,153
Even if they do snap
a picture of you,

169
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:37,720
I can always come up with
an excuse if it's elsewhere.

170
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,953
But if they get a picture of him
leaving your place,

171
00:12:40,033 --> 00:12:41,453
then there's absolutely
no excuse for that!

172
00:12:41,533 --> 00:12:43,220
Just leave this to us.

173
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:45,220
We're doing our best
so we're not busted!

174
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,053
If you said you'll pretend
you don't know we're dating,

175
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:48,320
then please, just do that!

176
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,633
Pretend you've seen nothing,
even if you did!

177
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:59,586
I'd like to do that too,

178
00:12:59,666 --> 00:13:01,386
but I'm still worried that
you'll be busted…

179
00:13:01,466 --> 00:13:04,020
And even if I did say I'll approve,
I can't quite, completely…

180
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:05,466
This is driving me nuts, too!

181
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:11,166
What are you looking at,
you stupid hedgehog?

182
00:13:21,566 --> 00:13:22,953
Oh what?

183
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:25,386
I didn't see you this morning
so I wondered where you were.

184
00:13:25,466 --> 00:13:26,733
You were out
playing soccer, were you?

185
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:31,666
But… "Singil 3-dong
Morning Soccer Club?"

186
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,633
Why'd you have to go so far?

187
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,986
They're a good team, are they?

188
00:13:38,066 --> 00:13:39,486
Can I come next time?

189
00:13:39,566 --> 00:13:41,853
You're never allowed there.

190
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,553
Why not?

191
00:13:43,633 --> 00:13:44,986
What,

192
00:13:45,066 --> 00:13:47,086
are they strict about
accepting new members?

193
00:13:47,166 --> 00:13:49,153
But I'm good at soccer!

194
00:13:49,233 --> 00:13:52,266
When I say no, just accept it.

195
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:56,320
What's wrong with him?

196
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:59,566
Why does he have to be
so cocky and stingy?

197
00:14:11,066 --> 00:14:12,133
(Singil 3-dong
Morning Soccer Club)

198
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,300
I can't believe what I've been
getting myself into.

199
00:14:29,966 --> 00:14:33,386
You said you'll be done around 7,
and I couldn't wait to see you.

200
00:14:33,466 --> 00:14:34,866
Are you done with
your shooting yet?

201
00:14:36,666 --> 00:14:40,066
We're almost done.
Shall we have dinner together?

202
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:42,386
Sure.

203
00:14:42,466 --> 00:14:44,833
Then see you at my place.

204
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:49,820
I won't end up being
soaked, will I?

205
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:50,853
Of course not.

206
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:54,233
I'm thinking of changing the
passcode as soon as I'm home.

207
00:14:55,933 --> 00:14:59,333
Then I'll get
your favorite, sushi.

208
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:14,086
Yes, Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

209
00:15:14,166 --> 00:15:15,453
- I just…
- What do I do?

210
00:15:15,533 --> 00:15:18,620
We'll be shooting some more
and so I'll be finishing late.

211
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:22,286
I don't think
I'll be able to see you tonight.

212
00:15:22,366 --> 00:15:25,086
I see… It can't be helped.

213
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:28,400
You didn't buy the
sushi already, did you?

214
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:31,786
No, not yet.

215
00:15:31,866 --> 00:15:34,200
Don't worry about me,
but good luck with your work.

216
00:15:35,133 --> 00:15:36,300
Bye, then.

217
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:57,866
I'm here.

218
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,120
Oh what?

219
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,720
Why are you having
two to yourself?

220
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,686
Oh, one's for me, is it?

221
00:16:07,766 --> 00:16:09,053
No, it isn't.

222
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:11,800
Then who did you buy it for?

223
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,586
They're both for me, so what?

224
00:16:14,666 --> 00:16:16,333
You're really selfish.

225
00:16:17,366 --> 00:16:19,786
You won’t let me into
that soccer club,

226
00:16:19,866 --> 00:16:22,066
and now you're having two packs of
sushi, all to yourself…

227
00:16:23,066 --> 00:16:24,220
Why have you changed so much?

228
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:25,400
It's not like that.

229
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:29,986
From now on,

230
00:16:30,066 --> 00:16:32,333
I'll teach you the joy of sharing.

231
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:35,753
Now watch and learn.

232
00:16:35,833 --> 00:16:37,700
Learn how to be
with others. Alright?

233
00:16:42,866 --> 00:16:44,720
Yes, that's right.

234
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,900
Eat up.

235
00:16:48,233 --> 00:16:49,553
So you had something to tell me.

236
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:50,753
What is it?

237
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,686
Well, it's really nothing.

238
00:16:52,766 --> 00:16:56,386
As you know, our actors have
been going beyond Korea

239
00:16:56,466 --> 00:16:58,586
and that means our contracts
have become global, too.

240
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:02,986
So I've been thinking, maybe
we should have a corporate lawyer.

241
00:17:03,066 --> 00:17:05,100
Oh!

242
00:17:06,133 --> 00:17:08,520
So you'd like to
partner up with our law firm, huh?

243
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:10,853
Well, though I understand
your wishes,

244
00:17:10,933 --> 00:17:13,086
I'm not sure if
that's quite possible.

245
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:15,520
- Eh?
- I'm sure you've, uh…

246
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:18,320
…heard about the Lim Yun-hee case
that everyone's talking about.

247
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,833
Who solved that case?

248
00:17:20,366 --> 00:17:22,733
We, Always, did.

249
00:17:24,933 --> 00:17:27,053
Hey, get your facts right.

250
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:28,153
How did Always solve it?

251
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:29,220
It was Kwon Jung-rok
who solved it.

252
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:31,286
That guy may be a prick,
but he's sure competent.

253
00:17:31,366 --> 00:17:32,400
Anyway,

254
00:17:33,766 --> 00:17:36,886
that's why our law firm is
now in high demand.

255
00:17:36,966 --> 00:17:40,986
Especially me, as the head of
that law firm in the spotlight.

256
00:17:41,066 --> 00:17:44,553
All the TV stations and
magazines are

257
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:46,520
desperate to interview me.

258
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,520
There hasn’t been a single place
that hasn't called me!

259
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,753
So… Will you do it, or no?

260
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,853
I'm not saying no.

261
00:17:52,933 --> 00:17:57,166
I'm just saying, we may not
have the capacity.

262
00:17:58,066 --> 00:18:01,020
So you don't have the
capacity… Too bad.

263
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:05,253
If you become our family,
then there are those

264
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:08,053
end-of-year parties with
our celebs… Cheers!

265
00:18:08,133 --> 00:18:12,020
Oh, and the summer camps on
the Waikiki beach…

266
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,720
Beach volleyball…!

267
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:14,800
Toss!

268
00:18:15,133 --> 00:18:16,553
I have it!

269
00:18:16,633 --> 00:18:18,486
You could've met them all.

270
00:18:18,566 --> 00:18:20,166
Too bad, then. Alright.

271
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:24,953
Jun-seok, Jun-seok…

272
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:27,286
My dear cousin!

273
00:18:27,366 --> 00:18:30,453
Where's your sense of humor?

274
00:18:30,533 --> 00:18:33,386
Did you think I would
really turn you down?

275
00:18:33,466 --> 00:18:36,553
I really don't know how you run
your business with your naivety.

276
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:38,286
Bring me the contract,
and I'll sign it right now.

277
00:18:38,366 --> 00:18:40,253
Aw, cousin…

278
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:42,120
Thanks, man.

279
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:46,120
By the way, the production team
of Yoon-seo's drama

280
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,920
wants an advisory lawyer.

281
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,020
Advisory lawyer?

282
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,253
You know. Those professionals

283
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:52,720
who join the set
and make sure that

284
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,686
all the legal jargons are correct.

285
00:18:54,766 --> 00:18:58,420
And they wanted someone
who's acquainted to Yoon-seo.

286
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,620
I can help.

287
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:00,733
Me, I'm available!

288
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:03,553
Right, you're a lawyer, too.

289
00:19:03,633 --> 00:19:05,053
Of course I am.

290
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:07,086
Too bad, though.

291
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:09,753
- Huh?
- You don't have the capacity.

292
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,653
Just find someone else
for me, then.

293
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:14,486
It's okay, cutie pie. I'll do it.

294
00:19:14,566 --> 00:19:16,186
No, no. I'm not sure
if I can trust you.

295
00:19:16,266 --> 00:19:19,186
What if you go to the set and

296
00:19:19,266 --> 00:19:21,753
end up making gif files like this?

297
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:24,020
Just find me someone else.

298
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:26,153
But no one else will
probably want to do it.

299
00:19:26,233 --> 00:19:27,653
An advisory lawyer?

300
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:28,733
Yes.

301
00:19:29,466 --> 00:19:30,553
So no one wants to do it?

302
00:19:30,633 --> 00:19:33,053
I guess it's tiring and
takes up too much time.

303
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:34,186
I mean, right?

304
00:19:34,266 --> 00:19:35,886
Yes, well…

305
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:38,386
I'm also busy with many cases,

306
00:19:38,466 --> 00:19:41,453
and I wouldn't want to be
approached by

307
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:44,786
casting managers…

308
00:19:44,866 --> 00:19:46,153
I'll pass, thank you.

309
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:49,553
Okay! Then it's decided, I'll go.

310
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:51,353
You must be happy, Mr. Yeon.

311
00:19:51,433 --> 00:19:53,986
Now you'll get to see
Yoon-seo more often.

312
00:19:54,066 --> 00:19:56,820
Right? I guess I'll be
seeing her often, huh?

313
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:58,686
They say they need one
starting today,

314
00:19:58,766 --> 00:20:01,320
so it's decided, I'll go.

315
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,400
No.

316
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:05,700
I'll go.

317
00:20:10,633 --> 00:20:12,853
I think I'm hearing things.

318
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:15,533
Kwon, can you repeat that again?

319
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:18,686
I said I'll go.

320
00:20:18,766 --> 00:20:19,933
For the advisory lawyer position.

321
00:20:23,433 --> 00:20:27,386
But you're not interested in
that kind of thing.

322
00:20:27,466 --> 00:20:29,186
No, but…

323
00:20:29,266 --> 00:20:32,400
I thought it wouldn't hurt,
for the experience.

324
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:37,120
Kwon, they say when you
act out of character,

325
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:39,420
you're only bringing
death upon you.

326
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:42,353
So just stay out of this
like you always have,

327
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,320
and continue fighting for justice.

328
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,686
No, I want to do it.
The advisory lawyer.

329
00:20:46,766 --> 00:20:48,786
Why do you have to say that?

330
00:20:48,866 --> 00:20:52,420
What, do you think
you've become a celebrity

331
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,686
after that interview from
a few days ago?

332
00:20:53,766 --> 00:20:55,486
Why are you suddenly
seeking so much attention?

333
00:20:55,566 --> 00:20:58,486
Seek attention? Then why even
agree to it in the first place?

334
00:20:58,566 --> 00:21:00,253
Whatever, fine.
Then let's have everyone vote.

335
00:21:00,333 --> 00:21:01,720
Vote?

336
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:04,353
Yes. Because if you make
a mistake while on the set,

337
00:21:04,433 --> 00:21:06,220
that'll be tainting us
Always' reputation.

338
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:10,020
So let's leave it to
our good citizens to decide

339
00:21:10,100 --> 00:21:17,166
who is better suited to
represent Always.

340
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,900
(Yeon Jun-gyu: 1 vote
Kwon Jung-rok: 4 votes)

341
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:30,533
Then I'll be off.

342
00:21:48,266 --> 00:21:50,620
Ms. Oh Jin-sim, listen to this.

343
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:52,920
We can finally see each other.

344
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,253
I'll be joining the set

345
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:57,266
as your advisory lawyer…

346
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:02,353
Actually, no.

347
00:22:02,433 --> 00:22:04,100
Let's surprise her.

348
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:16,020
Is it because I didn't get to see
Mr. Kwon last night?

349
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:19,966
I just don't have the
energy or the appetite.

350
00:22:22,066 --> 00:22:23,553
I see.

351
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:27,020
So that's why you left
two strands of radish.

352
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:29,100
I thought you had
washed this clean already.

353
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:32,700
When did I say
I didn't have the appetite?

354
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:35,186
You know, Yoon-seo…

355
00:22:35,266 --> 00:22:37,686
I really like how you eat so well.

356
00:22:37,766 --> 00:22:38,886
I really do, but…

357
00:22:38,966 --> 00:22:40,786
You need to watch your weight.

358
00:22:40,866 --> 00:22:43,786
What if you appear
all chubby on the camera?

359
00:22:43,866 --> 00:22:44,953
Oh, and…

360
00:22:45,033 --> 00:22:46,486
You know you have
a photoshoot next week, right?

361
00:22:46,566 --> 00:22:48,553
Yes, yes, I know. Don't worry.

362
00:22:48,633 --> 00:22:50,500
I have a conscience.

363
00:22:53,366 --> 00:22:55,686
For example, I'm drinking this
because it's supposed to help.

364
00:22:55,766 --> 00:22:57,320
Yes, good.

365
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,120
You know, you drinking that looks
like you're advertising for it.

366
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,433
Go on, drink more.

367
00:23:02,666 --> 00:23:05,433
- May I see you for a second?
- Oh, sure.

368
00:23:12,666 --> 00:23:14,900
Gosh, I miss Mr. Kwon.

369
00:23:16,333 --> 00:23:17,420
Who knew?

370
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:19,453
That Mr. Kwon would be
interested in that sort of thing.

371
00:23:19,533 --> 00:23:20,620
I know, right?

372
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:22,186
It's like seeing the mirage
of oasis in the desert.

373
00:23:22,266 --> 00:23:24,433
I still can't believe what I saw.

374
00:23:27,266 --> 00:23:28,453
Oh, so there you are.

375
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:29,600
Having tea?

376
00:23:31,166 --> 00:23:32,200
Looks delicious.

377
00:23:33,766 --> 00:23:39,120
By the way, I'd like someone to
keep meeting minutes from now on.

378
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,120
It can be a bit loud
on the keyboard,

379
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:44,586
so I'd like someone to
write it down instead.

380
00:23:44,666 --> 00:23:45,986
Sure, I'll do it.

381
00:23:46,066 --> 00:23:47,986
Oh, Hae-young. But do you have
good handwriting?

382
00:23:48,066 --> 00:23:48,986
Yes.

383
00:23:49,066 --> 00:23:50,220
Because I'd like it to be

384
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:53,020
someone with fine handwriting.

385
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:54,353
- Uh…
- Just to be sure,

386
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:56,786
why don't we all write down
something and see?

387
00:23:56,866 --> 00:23:59,486
Everyone, write "meeting minutes."

388
00:23:59,566 --> 00:24:01,020
"Meeting minutes."

389
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:03,833
It's best to leave it to
the best person, right?

390
00:24:13,433 --> 00:24:15,200
(Meeting minutes)

391
00:24:20,466 --> 00:24:22,453
There you are. I see!

392
00:24:22,533 --> 00:24:25,233
So that's who you are.

393
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:29,966
Choi, Dan, Hae-young, Ms. Yang…

394
00:24:30,300 --> 00:24:32,666
I'm so disappointed.
I trusted you guys!

395
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:34,486
I was so good to you,

396
00:24:34,566 --> 00:24:36,800
yet you betray me
and vote for Kwon?

397
00:24:37,766 --> 00:24:39,586
What… What do you mean?

398
00:24:39,666 --> 00:24:41,286
I voted for you, Mr. Yeon.

399
00:24:41,366 --> 00:24:43,100
You had one vote, right?

400
00:24:43,300 --> 00:24:44,320
Well, that was from me.

401
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,853
Whatever!

402
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:47,220
Look here.

403
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:50,020
Compare "Kwon Jung-rok" with the

404
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:52,620
"meeting minutes"
you all just wrote down,

405
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:54,920
and this is the only
handwriting I'm not seeing.

406
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,020
This is the only one.

407
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:59,333
I see you were in
a dilemma, Ms. Yang.

408
00:25:00,366 --> 00:25:01,953
You said voting would be
kept confidential.

409
00:25:02,033 --> 00:25:03,253
So you can't just do this!

410
00:25:03,333 --> 00:25:05,353
Well, who cares?
I was just curious.

411
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:08,320
Besides, I never said
there'll be any disadvantages.

412
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:11,186
By the way, why's it
so dusty in the office?

413
00:25:11,266 --> 00:25:13,320
Why don't we all come in
on the weekend and

414
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,486
have a massive clean-up?

415
00:25:15,566 --> 00:25:17,166
Except for you, Mr. Lee.

416
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:18,686
I'll give you a movie ticket,

417
00:25:18,766 --> 00:25:20,066
so go watch a movie instead.

418
00:25:29,266 --> 00:25:30,320
Good morning. Good morning.

419
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,453
Ah, Yoon-seo.

420
00:25:31,533 --> 00:25:32,786
- Hello.
- Oh, um…

421
00:25:32,866 --> 00:25:34,966
Our new advisory lawyer is here.

422
00:25:48,366 --> 00:25:51,233
Mr. Kwon, can you take
a look at the script?

423
00:25:53,766 --> 00:25:54,900
(Waiting Room/Oh Yoon-seo)

424
00:25:55,833 --> 00:25:57,986
What… How…?

425
00:25:58,066 --> 00:25:59,420
How did you come here?

426
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:02,120
You're the advisory lawyer for
our drama?

427
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:05,353
It wasn't an easy path to
being voted the advisory lawyer.

428
00:26:05,433 --> 00:26:06,353
Voted?

429
00:26:06,433 --> 00:26:10,186
Yes. Mr. Yeon, who enjoys
attention from the media,

430
00:26:10,266 --> 00:26:12,353
couldn't have made
his ambitions more clear about

431
00:26:12,433 --> 00:26:13,886
being the advisory lawyer for
your drama, Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

432
00:26:13,966 --> 00:26:16,520
But determined to
see you no matter what,

433
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,753
I withstood his temptations
and his criticisms,

434
00:26:18,833 --> 00:26:21,153
and as a result, it was decided
it'll come down to voting.

435
00:26:21,233 --> 00:26:23,320
And so, through what was
a landslide vote of 4:1,

436
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,786
I, Kwon Jung-rok,

437
00:26:24,866 --> 00:26:28,600
was proudly voted
your team's advisory lawyer!

438
00:26:30,966 --> 00:26:32,053
Even when I look back now,

439
00:26:32,133 --> 00:26:34,666
it was a very close call indeed.

440
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:38,653
It does sound so dramatic.

441
00:26:38,733 --> 00:26:39,853
Yes.

442
00:26:39,933 --> 00:26:42,186
But after coming here
and seeing you like this,

443
00:26:42,266 --> 00:26:44,900
I'm glad I stood for candidacy.

444
00:26:46,066 --> 00:26:48,753
But, uh… I hope me being here

445
00:26:48,833 --> 00:26:50,020
isn't putting you in trouble
or making you uncomfortable…

446
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:51,653
No way!

447
00:26:51,733 --> 00:26:54,386
You've no idea
how happy I am right now.

448
00:26:54,466 --> 00:26:57,600
I missed you so much, too.

449
00:26:59,700 --> 00:27:01,266
Yoon-seo, are you in here?

450
00:27:04,633 --> 00:27:06,000
I'm really sorry.

451
00:27:06,566 --> 00:27:07,786
Are you, uh… Actually, no.

452
00:27:07,866 --> 00:27:09,520
Yoon-seo. Oh Yoon-seo!

453
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:10,600
Yes?

454
00:27:10,766 --> 00:27:12,720
We need to start now.
So come on, hurry up!

455
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,753
Sure, sure. I'll get going.

456
00:27:14,833 --> 00:27:16,853
Um… Mr. Kwon, you better come too.

457
00:27:16,933 --> 00:27:17,933
Alright.

458
00:27:20,300 --> 00:27:21,300
What was that for?

459
00:27:23,933 --> 00:27:27,186
Mr. Kwon, I understand
how you feel,

460
00:27:27,266 --> 00:27:29,953
but coming here as
the advisory lawyer is…

461
00:27:30,033 --> 00:27:31,420
I have free will and the
freedom to do so.

462
00:27:31,500 --> 00:27:32,586
Besides, interfering with
everything we do is

463
00:27:32,666 --> 00:27:33,820
infringing on
our rights to happiness

464
00:27:33,900 --> 00:27:35,620
and our right to act freely,

465
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:37,786
both of which are guaranteed by
the Constitutional Law.

466
00:27:37,866 --> 00:27:38,866
Then please excuse me.

467
00:27:39,666 --> 00:27:40,700
Sure.

468
00:27:42,766 --> 00:27:43,920
Yoon-seo, don't go!

469
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:45,500
Not just you two, together!
Wait up for me!

470
00:27:46,966 --> 00:27:51,620
You testified that you were
at home on that day.

471
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:52,800
Is this true?

472
00:27:55,433 --> 00:27:56,966
Your Honor.

473
00:28:00,866 --> 00:28:01,786
Sorry, one moment.

474
00:28:01,866 --> 00:28:04,486
Um… Mr. Kwon?

475
00:28:04,566 --> 00:28:06,520
When I say, "Your Honor,"

476
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:10,286
what should I do with my hand?

477
00:28:10,366 --> 00:28:12,220
Oh, uh..

478
00:28:12,300 --> 00:28:13,333
Please.

479
00:28:13,666 --> 00:28:14,700
Sure.

480
00:28:17,866 --> 00:28:20,866
Instead of pointing at the judge
directly like this,

481
00:28:21,366 --> 00:28:24,986
stand straight, or gather your
hands to the front, politely.

482
00:28:25,066 --> 00:28:26,733
I think this will look better.

483
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,220
Not like this?

484
00:28:29,300 --> 00:28:31,186
No, both hands would be too…

485
00:28:31,266 --> 00:28:32,600
Stand straight, or…

486
00:28:39,566 --> 00:28:41,166
Your Honor!

487
00:28:44,466 --> 00:28:45,453
Mr. Kwon,

488
00:28:45,533 --> 00:28:46,853
here you are.

489
00:28:46,933 --> 00:28:47,933
Thank you.

490
00:28:52,100 --> 00:28:54,666
Um, Mr. Kwon.

491
00:28:56,066 --> 00:28:58,453
I'm a little bothered by
this part on the script.

492
00:28:58,533 --> 00:29:01,333
Is this expression okay?

493
00:29:02,866 --> 00:29:04,100
(Kwon Jung-rok)

494
00:29:08,566 --> 00:29:12,033
Yes, that's absolutely correct.

495
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,000
I see.

496
00:29:15,566 --> 00:29:16,953
Yep, that's right.

497
00:29:17,033 --> 00:29:19,686
From how I see it,
this script is absolutely perfect.

498
00:29:19,766 --> 00:29:21,466
So can we move onto
the next scene already?

499
00:29:21,666 --> 00:29:22,900
You… Follow me.

500
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,200
Ms. Dan.

501
00:29:53,233 --> 00:29:54,620
Though our contract dating's over,

502
00:29:54,700 --> 00:29:56,353
we're still colleagues, aren't we?

503
00:29:56,433 --> 00:29:58,586
So why do you have to
ignore me like this?

504
00:29:58,666 --> 00:29:59,786
Oh, did I?

505
00:29:59,866 --> 00:30:02,666
If I did, I'm sorry.

506
00:30:03,133 --> 00:30:04,133
Wait.

507
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:09,086
Is it going well with
that delivery guy

508
00:30:09,166 --> 00:30:11,120
- you chased after that time?
- No.

509
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:13,286
That was just my drunk habit,

510
00:30:13,366 --> 00:30:14,953
and it's nothing
serious with him, really.

511
00:30:15,033 --> 00:30:19,653
Anyway, I'm sorry
I failed to keep that clause about

512
00:30:19,733 --> 00:30:22,420
how I won't fall for someone else

513
00:30:22,500 --> 00:30:24,586
during the term of the contract.

514
00:30:24,666 --> 00:30:26,853
Of course you should be.

515
00:30:26,933 --> 00:30:27,920
Well,

516
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:31,420
I don't think you have
the right to say that.

517
00:30:31,500 --> 00:30:34,386
You said
your heart doesn't move.

518
00:30:34,466 --> 00:30:35,920
So what's the point of

519
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,653
continuing on
this contract relationship with

520
00:30:37,733 --> 00:30:39,386
someone who continues to
feel nothing for me?

521
00:30:39,466 --> 00:30:41,553
I'll just end up…

522
00:30:41,633 --> 00:30:42,620
…hurt.

