00:46:55,100 --> 00:46:56,653
After her trial,
Ju-ha steps out of the court,

788
00:46:56,733 --> 00:46:58,153
and is met with surprise.

789
00:46:58,233 --> 00:47:01,433
Jung-do is standing there,
in his uniform…"

790
00:47:02,533 --> 00:47:04,766
"Jung-do takes Ju-ha's hand, and…

791
00:47:08,366 --> 00:47:10,000
…kisses her."

792
00:47:12,333 --> 00:47:15,233
"The two kiss with the court
in the background."

793
00:47:21,300 --> 00:47:23,700
(Kiss Expert)

794
00:47:31,966 --> 00:47:33,666
"Kiss expert," huh?

795
00:47:35,500 --> 00:47:37,020
Oh, uh…

796
00:47:37,100 --> 00:47:41,386
I reserved that beef barbecue place
in front for dinner.

797
00:47:41,466 --> 00:47:43,386
Yes, good job!

798
00:47:43,466 --> 00:47:45,220
The raw beef there is
a work of art.

799
00:47:45,300 --> 00:47:48,286
I say the chef there is
a beef expert!

800
00:47:48,366 --> 00:47:49,753
Expert?

801
00:47:49,833 --> 00:47:52,320
There's no such thing as
a kiss expert!

802
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:54,433
What, the chef is a kiss expert?

803
00:47:57,866 --> 00:47:58,886
It's nothing.

804
00:47:58,966 --> 00:47:59,986
I'll get going first.

805
00:48:00,066 --> 00:48:01,553
What, you're not going to
finish your meal?

806
00:48:01,633 --> 00:48:03,966
No. I have to be at the court now.

807
00:48:05,400 --> 00:48:06,820
"Kiss expert..."

808
00:48:06,900 --> 00:48:08,853
That's what he said.

809
00:48:08,933 --> 00:48:11,066
He said "kiss" something,
didn't he?

810
00:48:12,333 --> 00:48:15,786
Does Kwon want a girlfriend?

811
00:48:15,866 --> 00:48:17,053
But then again,

812
00:48:17,133 --> 00:48:20,453
it's spring and
love is in the air…

813
00:48:20,533 --> 00:48:22,700
Even Kwon would want one.

814
00:48:24,733 --> 00:48:27,453
Hold on. Everyone here is
single, right?

815
00:48:27,533 --> 00:48:28,620
There's so many of us here,

816
00:48:28,700 --> 00:48:30,666
and not one is in a relationship?

817
00:48:31,833 --> 00:48:33,753
If you don't have time to
go out and find one,

818
00:48:33,833 --> 00:48:36,486
then look for one here.

819
00:48:36,566 --> 00:48:39,520
There's plenty of office dating
in other companies,

820
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:42,820
so why haven't I heard of
one in our company?

821
00:48:42,900 --> 00:48:45,586
I thought you don't really
approve of office dating.

822
00:48:45,666 --> 00:48:47,120
Because you're worried we won't
concentrate on work.

823
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:50,086
Hey, I'm not that old-fashioned.

824
00:48:50,166 --> 00:48:51,486
You know what?

825
00:48:51,566 --> 00:48:54,320
If I ever see
a couple being born here,

826
00:48:54,400 --> 00:48:55,586
I'll buy both of them new suits to

827
00:48:55,666 --> 00:48:57,466
cheer on for their relationship.

828
00:48:58,300 --> 00:49:00,220
So as soon as you start dating,

829
00:49:00,300 --> 00:49:02,800
raise your hand and report it.

830
00:49:05,533 --> 00:49:07,353
- What are you two doing?
- You said to report it.

831
00:49:07,433 --> 00:49:09,620
Ms. Dan and I are dating.

832
00:49:09,700 --> 00:49:13,733
Right, though we only just
started dating since yesterday.

833
00:49:14,766 --> 00:49:15,853
Oh, come on!

834
00:49:15,933 --> 00:49:18,053
What do you think
you two are trying here?

835
00:49:18,133 --> 00:49:19,620
I get you both want free suits,

836
00:49:19,700 --> 00:49:20,886
but you two, dating?
It doesn't make sense!

837
00:49:20,966 --> 00:49:23,166
Hey, it's not even funny.

838
00:49:31,833 --> 00:49:33,833
What… You're really dating?

839
00:49:37,166 --> 00:49:39,033
I've been stabbed
right in the back!

840
00:49:43,700 --> 00:49:45,700
(Court)

841
00:49:47,866 --> 00:49:51,066
The whole team's there,
so she should be here, too.

842
00:49:57,433 --> 00:49:58,553
Yoon-seo.

843
00:49:58,633 --> 00:50:01,153
What do you plan to do here?

844
00:50:01,233 --> 00:50:03,053
Just do what you want,
and I'll try to follow.

845
00:50:03,133 --> 00:50:04,120
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

846
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:05,333
Alright, then.

847
00:50:08,500 --> 00:50:09,533
Huh?

848
00:50:11,966 --> 00:50:13,033
Mr. Kwon!

849
00:50:14,200 --> 00:50:15,200
Ah, yes.

850
00:50:16,800 --> 00:50:18,620
What brings you here?

851
00:50:18,700 --> 00:50:20,653
I had business here,

852
00:50:20,733 --> 00:50:21,953
when I heard
you'll be shooting here.

853
00:50:22,033 --> 00:50:24,000
So here I am, in case you need me.

854
00:50:26,300 --> 00:50:28,253
I'm glad we're shooting
at the court today.

855
00:50:28,333 --> 00:50:30,386
We got to bump into
each other like this.

856
00:50:30,466 --> 00:50:33,033
- Yes.
- Yoon-seo, we're starting!

857
00:50:40,166 --> 00:50:42,320
I'll get going then, Mr. Kwon.

858
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:43,400
Sure.

859
00:50:53,133 --> 00:50:54,166
Jung-do.

860
00:50:56,933 --> 00:50:58,286
How did you…

861
00:50:58,366 --> 00:51:00,486
I thought you're in Asrael.

862
00:51:00,566 --> 00:51:02,220
I came, because
I didn't want to regret it.

863
00:51:02,300 --> 00:51:05,566
I didn't want to regret
letting you go, Ju-ha.

864
00:51:22,600 --> 00:51:23,553
Cut!

865
00:51:23,633 --> 00:51:24,853
Oh what?

866
00:51:24,933 --> 00:51:27,253
Did you hear that car?

867
00:51:27,333 --> 00:51:29,920
Please remove that for me.

868
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:32,120
Alright, everyone on standby.

869
00:51:32,200 --> 00:51:34,800
Um… wait!

870
00:51:37,533 --> 00:51:40,186
May I offer advice,
as the advisory lawyer?

871
00:51:40,266 --> 00:51:41,786
Sure, go ahead.

872
00:51:41,866 --> 00:51:43,186
I know this is a drama,

873
00:51:43,266 --> 00:51:45,453
but I think the two kissing
in front of the court is

874
00:51:45,533 --> 00:51:48,033
too out of touch with the reality.

875
00:51:48,333 --> 00:51:49,453
Besides, we're talking
about a lawyer,

876
00:51:49,533 --> 00:51:51,086
who is the guardian of justice,
and a military judicial officer!

877
00:51:51,166 --> 00:51:53,786
So kissing in front of
the sacred court?

878
00:51:53,866 --> 00:51:56,086
As someone in this industry,

879
00:51:56,166 --> 00:51:59,220
I think this is
pushing it too far.

880
00:51:59,300 --> 00:52:01,366
We're all very conservative.

881
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:07,433
Still, if you think this needs
to be an emotional scene…

882
00:52:09,033 --> 00:52:11,186
A hug! I think a hug will do.

883
00:52:11,266 --> 00:52:13,586
- A hug?
- Actually, no.

884
00:52:13,666 --> 00:52:14,766
Not even a hug.

885
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:18,153
A handshake! Yes, a handshake.

886
00:52:18,233 --> 00:52:20,053
I think a handshake is enough.

887
00:52:20,133 --> 00:52:22,666
Mr. Kwon? How about
you join me for coffee?

888
00:52:23,033 --> 00:52:24,053
I'm alright.

889
00:52:24,133 --> 00:52:26,300
No, I think you should join me.

890
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:31,186
Just now, you told me to back off,

891
00:52:31,266 --> 00:52:34,353
saying I was infringing on your
rights to happiness or whatnot.

892
00:52:34,433 --> 00:52:37,586
Yet what was that just now?

893
00:52:37,666 --> 00:52:40,486
I was simply doing my job
as an advisory lawyer.

894
00:52:40,566 --> 00:52:43,220
If you're here as an
advisory lawyer, then do your job,

895
00:52:43,300 --> 00:52:45,753
instead of being jealous!

896
00:52:45,833 --> 00:52:46,953
I wasn't jealous.

897
00:52:47,033 --> 00:52:48,900
You were jealous.

898
00:52:50,100 --> 00:52:51,420
I mean, look.

899
00:52:51,500 --> 00:52:52,753
Look at them, Mr. Kwon.

900
00:52:52,833 --> 00:52:55,720
Just now, you went on about
how everyone's all conservative,

901
00:52:55,800 --> 00:52:57,553
but look at those two,
holding hands in public!

902
00:52:57,633 --> 00:52:59,333
What happened to the
"conservative," huh?

903
00:53:00,333 --> 00:53:01,753
But… That's not normal.

904
00:53:01,833 --> 00:53:05,366
Everyone in law is
very conservative, and…

905
00:53:08,466 --> 00:53:09,500
…Kim se-won?

906
00:53:11,033 --> 00:53:13,386
Ah, Jung-rok.

907
00:53:13,466 --> 00:53:14,600
Jung-rok?

908
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:17,233
What, they're even
your acquaintances?

909
00:53:19,100 --> 00:53:20,020
I don't know them.

910
00:53:20,100 --> 00:53:21,286
Kim Se-won!

911
00:53:21,366 --> 00:53:22,653
Jung-rok!

912
00:53:22,733 --> 00:53:23,886
I'll exercise my right to
remain silent.

913
00:53:23,966 --> 00:53:25,933
Look at you, so jealous!

914
00:53:29,966 --> 00:53:31,786
Are you two allowed to
hold hands like that

915
00:53:31,866 --> 00:53:33,920
in your gowns, at court?

916
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:34,920
Who cares?

917
00:53:35,000 --> 00:53:36,920
It's not like us dating is
affecting work.

918
00:53:37,000 --> 00:53:40,000
Besides, we were tired of
keeping it a secret forever.

919
00:53:40,466 --> 00:53:44,620
We decided to stop caring about
what other people think.

920
00:53:44,700 --> 00:53:48,486
Same here. I wouldn't have
ever thought of doing this,

921
00:53:48,566 --> 00:53:50,686
but Se-won's right.

922
00:53:50,766 --> 00:53:51,720
It's always hard the first time,

923
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:54,266
but keep at it,
and it's really nothing.

924
00:53:55,366 --> 00:53:56,586
Jung-rok.

925
00:53:56,666 --> 00:53:58,020
What do I do?

926
00:53:58,100 --> 00:54:00,366
I guess I'm becoming
just like him.

927
00:54:02,766 --> 00:54:04,000
Sure, sure.

928
00:54:30,700 --> 00:54:32,586
Alright, here's to…

929
00:54:32,666 --> 00:54:34,000
- Always!
- To Always!

930
00:54:41,366 --> 00:54:44,353
So, how did you two
end up together?

931
00:54:44,433 --> 00:54:47,820
Right, you were the
worst of enemies.

932
00:54:47,900 --> 00:54:50,120
Let's be honest,
I'm not saying this because

933
00:54:50,200 --> 00:54:52,953
he's my boyfriend, but
Mr. Choi was born to be loved!

934
00:54:53,033 --> 00:54:54,220
He's handsome,

935
00:54:54,300 --> 00:54:56,286
competent, and is a gentleman.

936
00:54:56,366 --> 00:54:57,386
Not only that,
he's such a filial son.

937
00:54:57,466 --> 00:55:00,020
He really is the perfect man!

938
00:55:00,100 --> 00:55:01,820
Same with Ms. Dan.

939
00:55:01,900 --> 00:55:04,200
Sometimes she's cute,
sometimes she's just so chic.

940
00:55:04,700 --> 00:55:06,933
She's a woman with
a thousand charms!

941
00:55:08,133 --> 00:55:09,253
Sure.

942
00:55:09,333 --> 00:55:11,553
Though I can't quite
agree with what you said,

943
00:55:11,633 --> 00:55:13,466
a promise is a promise.

944
00:55:15,333 --> 00:55:18,320
Here, go buy yourselves new suits.

945
00:55:18,400 --> 00:55:19,620
Thank you, Mr. Yeon.

946
00:55:19,700 --> 00:55:21,786
Should we get matching suits?

947
00:55:21,866 --> 00:55:24,800
Something lovely,
that will suit you perfectly?

948
00:55:25,700 --> 00:55:26,653
No, no.

949
00:55:26,733 --> 00:55:28,620
Let's go for something
classic and chic,

950
00:55:28,700 --> 00:55:30,886
that suits you perfectly.

951
00:55:30,966 --> 00:55:32,186
Honey…

952
00:55:32,266 --> 00:55:33,266
Here.

953
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:36,386
I don't know why
I'm paying money to

954
00:55:36,466 --> 00:55:38,566
watch you two like that.

955
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:40,986
Anyway, if there are
any other couples

956
00:55:41,066 --> 00:55:41,786
who are yet to come out,
here's your chance.

957
00:55:41,866 --> 00:55:43,120
In fact, why don't you all

958
00:55:43,200 --> 00:55:44,820
use this chance to
get matching suits?

959
00:55:44,900 --> 00:55:46,320
I have a big loan to
pay off anyway,

960
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:48,153
and whether it's 700 grand
or 770 grand,

961
00:55:48,233 --> 00:55:49,533
there's not much
difference, is there?

962
00:55:50,433 --> 00:55:53,820
Um, Hae-young…
How about we use this chance

963
00:55:53,900 --> 00:55:55,553
and get matching suits?

964
00:55:55,633 --> 00:55:57,100
I have plenty, thank you.

965
00:56:09,366 --> 00:56:11,353
So, uh… Mr. Kwon.

966
00:56:11,433 --> 00:56:13,600
Is something up?

967
00:56:14,900 --> 00:56:16,486
Right.

968
00:56:16,566 --> 00:56:18,700
You don't look so good.

969
00:56:20,366 --> 00:56:22,753
Don't tell me that you'd been
secretly in love with Dan,

970
00:56:22,833 --> 00:56:24,853
but now that she's going out
with Choi, you're all heartbroken

971
00:56:24,933 --> 00:56:27,853
and that's why you're
drinking in silence, like this!

972
00:56:27,933 --> 00:56:29,686
Is that true?

973
00:56:29,766 --> 00:56:32,353
Unrequited love is still love.
I'll be rooting for you.

974
00:56:32,433 --> 00:56:33,766
Oh, no…

975
00:56:41,733 --> 00:56:43,900
Mr. Kwon, are you still having
dinner with everyone?

976
00:56:45,866 --> 00:56:47,053
I see.

977
00:56:47,133 --> 00:56:49,633
I just got off,
and I'm on my way home.

978
00:56:51,466 --> 00:56:54,000
Then call me, once you're done.

979
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:56,066
Alright.

980
00:56:57,800 --> 00:56:59,353
Did Mr. Kwon say anything?

981
00:56:59,433 --> 00:57:01,486
Say anything?

982
00:57:01,566 --> 00:57:03,333
- Why?
- Well, uh…

983
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:07,386
Back then,

984
00:57:07,466 --> 00:57:11,453
he was all jealous over
that kiss scene,

985
00:57:11,533 --> 00:57:13,053
so I told him
he's taking it too far.

986
00:57:13,133 --> 00:57:14,986
I'm worried that
he took it to heart.

987
00:57:15,066 --> 00:57:16,066
Huh?

988
00:57:18,766 --> 00:57:20,920
But then again, that's the
price of dating a celebrity.

989
00:57:21,000 --> 00:57:23,786
You need to pretend you're fine
with your girlfriend's kiss scene,

990
00:57:23,866 --> 00:57:26,320
but really, you're jealous…

991
00:57:26,400 --> 00:57:28,886
And it's not like you can tell
anyone you're dating her,

992
00:57:28,966 --> 00:57:32,266
let alone be seen with her
in public.

993
00:57:33,666 --> 00:57:35,753
Yoon-seo,

994
00:57:35,833 --> 00:57:38,553
this is why I'm worried.

995
00:57:38,633 --> 00:57:41,120
I'm worried whether
you two will be okay.

996
00:57:41,200 --> 00:57:43,053
Because dating in secret…

997
00:57:43,133 --> 00:57:45,633
You're bound to get tired of it
sometime or later.

998
00:57:53,666 --> 00:57:55,300
Here. Honey, say ah!

999
00:57:58,800 --> 00:58:00,333
You two, honey. Ah!

1000
00:58:02,766 --> 00:58:05,366
Love is blooming in Always.

1001
00:58:06,466 --> 00:58:07,720
Well…

1002
00:58:07,800 --> 00:58:10,986
For me, rage is
blooming in my heart.

1003
00:58:11,066 --> 00:58:12,153
You know what?

1004
00:58:12,233 --> 00:58:13,820
After watching those two,

1005
00:58:13,900 --> 00:58:16,886
I think I now know why
CEOs hate office dating.

1006
00:58:16,966 --> 00:58:18,420
I mean, what has the
CEO done so wrong to

1007
00:58:18,500 --> 00:58:20,653
pay them and
watch them be like that?

1008
00:58:20,733 --> 00:58:23,820
You know, all this stress is
going to make me ill,

1009
00:58:23,900 --> 00:58:25,553
so if you're all done, let's go.

1010
00:58:25,633 --> 00:58:26,633
Let's go, then.

1011
00:58:28,466 --> 00:58:30,086
- Ah, Yoon-seo!
- Hello.

1012
00:58:30,166 --> 00:58:31,853
Yoon-seo.

1013
00:58:31,933 --> 00:58:33,433
What brings you here?

1014
00:58:34,266 --> 00:58:36,786
I heard you guys were
having a group dinner here,

1015
00:58:36,866 --> 00:58:38,153
so here I am!

1016
00:58:38,233 --> 00:58:40,253
Great timing.
We were only getting started.

1017
00:58:40,333 --> 00:58:41,600
This way, please.

1018
00:58:43,266 --> 00:58:44,400
This way.

1019
00:58:48,300 --> 00:58:49,786
Jong-hwa, where was
your seat again?

1020
00:58:49,866 --> 00:58:51,966
- Over there.
- Right?

1021
00:58:55,033 --> 00:58:56,520
Yoon-seo, Yoon-seo!

1022
00:58:56,600 --> 00:58:58,186
We have big news.

1023
00:58:58,266 --> 00:59:00,420
And it's that…

1024
00:59:00,500 --> 00:59:01,700
Ms. Dan and Mr. Choi are dating!

1025
00:59:03,166 --> 00:59:05,486
- What, really?
- Yes, we are.

1026
00:59:05,566 --> 00:59:09,066
We were planning to tell you soon.

1027
00:59:10,066 --> 00:59:11,620
Wow, congratulations!

1028
00:59:11,700 --> 00:59:12,886
Kwon.

1029
00:59:12,966 --> 00:59:14,286
Aren't you happy to see Yoon-seo?

1030
00:59:14,366 --> 00:59:15,720
Why are you all silent?

1031
00:59:15,800 --> 00:59:16,886
- Pardon?
- Oh what?

1032
00:59:16,966 --> 00:59:18,120
Are you sure
nothing's up with you?

1033
00:59:18,200 --> 00:59:19,900
You look all down.

1034
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:22,553
Is it because it's spring?

1035
00:59:22,633 --> 00:59:24,066
You're lonely, aren't you?

1036
00:59:24,500 --> 00:59:26,186
- Is that why?
- What…

1037
00:59:26,266 --> 00:59:27,853
What do you mean, what?

1038
00:59:27,933 --> 00:59:30,766
Actually, why don't we
set up a blind date for him?

1039
00:59:32,400 --> 00:59:33,486
I'll pass, thank you.

1040
00:59:33,566 --> 00:59:34,520
What do you mean?

1041
00:59:34,600 --> 00:59:35,920
It's obvious you're still single.

1042
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:38,820
Take the chance when
it's offered to you, alright?

1043
00:59:38,900 --> 00:59:40,686
Hae-young, Dan!

